Apache is an HTTP server, otherwise called web server software. Other HTTP server software exists.

*Installing the Apache Web Server*

1. Update and upgarade system (sudo apt update , sudo apt -y upgrade)
2. install appache2 (sudo apt install apache2)
3. check system (systemctl list-unit-files apache2.service , systemctl status apache2)
4. install w3m (sudo apt install w3m)
5.check site (w3m localhost)
6. move to htlm path (cd /var/www/html/)
7. create new and renamed index.html (sudo mv index.html index.html.original)
8. expand index.html (sudo nano index.html)
9. Import basic HTML code that will be be shown to users/visitors on the site
10. Visit HTML site created (http://00.000.00.000/index.html.original)
